snippet.textDisplay: Back in college I once ordered from Pizza Hut, and about an hour after I received my order, I got a phone call from some guy saying he wanted to be my “very best friend.“ I did not know who it was, and when I asked, it turned out it was the delivery driver, who had gotten my phone number off of the receipt! I told him I wasn’t interested, and that I did not want him calling me. He persisted. He told me that he could “tell I was very special,“ and that he was supposed to be a part of my life. I threatened to call the manager of the store if he ever contacted  me again, and spent the rest of the evening terrified that this fool knew both my phone number and exactly where I lived. As a college student I was scared shitless, but as an adult woman, to this day, I regret never realizing I could/should have sued Pizza Hut for the invasion of privacy and threat to my personal safety.
